Class S3Location

java.lang.Object
jeroenflvr.csvprocessor.model.S3Location
public class S3Location extends Object
Immutable representation of an S3 or Cloud Object Storage (COS) location.

This class encapsulates the bucket and key components of an S3-style object storage location. It supports parsing various URI formats including standard S3 URIs, COS URIs, and simple bucket/key notation.

Supported URI formats:

  • s3://bucket-name/path/to/object.csv
  • cos://bucket-name/path/to/object.csv
  • bucket-name/path/to/object.csv

The class automatically handles leading slashes in object keys to ensure consistent key formatting regardless of input format.

  • Method Details

    • parse

      public static S3Location parse(String path)
      Parses a path string into an S3Location instance.

      This method supports multiple URI formats for maximum flexibility:

      • S3 URI: s3://bucket-name/path/to/file
      • COS URI: cos://bucket-name/path/to/file
      • Simple format: bucket-name/path/to/file

      The parser automatically extracts the bucket name and object key, handling edge cases such as missing keys or malformed URIs.

      Parameters:
      path - the path string to parse (must not be null)
      Returns:
      a new S3Location instance representing the parsed path
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the path format is invalid or missing required components
      NullPointerException - if path is null

      Example usage: 

       S3Location loc1 = S3Location.parse("s3://my-bucket/data/file.csv");
 S3Location loc2 = S3Location.parse("cos://my-bucket/data/file.csv");
 S3Location loc3 = S3Location.parse("my-bucket/data/file.csv");

    • getKey

      public String getKey()
      Gets the object key within the S3 bucket.

      The returned key will never have a leading slash, regardless of the input format used during parsing.

      Returns:
      the object key (never null, never starts with '/')
